The paper deals with rate-distortion with two decoders and side information, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The source and side information are jointly Gaussian vectors, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses lower bounds on the optimal rate, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
